<div class="div4"> NIKOL</div>
<p >
    
<h3>1. Location & Connectivity 🌍</h3>
<ul>
<li>Lies along Sardar Patel Ring Road and NH‑48, providing smooth access to central Ahmedabad, Vadodara, Gandhinagar, and the airport 


<li>The nearby Naroda Railway Station (~10 min) and AMTS/BRTS buses, along with auto-rickshaws, ensure convenient intra- and inter-city travel 


<li>Just ~8–12 km from Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel International Airport 
</ul>
<h3>  2. Infrastructure & Amenities 🏠</h3>
<ul>
<li>Residential: Mix of independent houses, apartments, villas; prices ~₹3 000–₹5 000 / sq ft 


<li>Rental market: 1 BHK for ~₹3 000; 2 BHK ~₹14 000; 3 BHK ~₹20 000/month .

<li>Schools: Dipak School, Central Public School, Sahajanand ICSE, Divine International, Sankalp International, Vedant International 


<li>Hospitals: Harmony, Parikh, Akshar, Mahavir, Satyamev, Dev Hospital, Gitanjali Children’s, Radhe Hospital 


<li>Shopping & Leisure: Nikol Plaza, Radhika Mall, Pavilion Mall, Pancham Mall, Inspire Fashion, local cafes and multiplexes 
</ul>
<h3> 3.  Growth & Real Estate Trends 📈</h3>
<ul>
<li>Rapid development since around 2008; considered prime for real estate growth 


<li>Prices rose ~15% last year; +72% over 10 years 


<li>Growing investor interest driven by affordability and connectivity 

</ul>
<h3> 4.  Living Experience & Local Feedback 🏡</h3>
<ul>
Rated around 4.3–4.6 stars, praised for peaceful vibe, good roads, safety, green spaces .

<li>Common positives: well-lit streets, CCTV coverage, family-friendly parks, community spirit 

<li>Challenges: peak-hour traffic congestion, parking scarcity, occasional waterlogging and power cuts during monsoon 
</ul>
<h3>5.  Notable Nearby Landmarks 🕌</h3>
<ul>
<li>Jhulta Mandir at Bibi-ji Masjid (shaking minarets) — iconic heritage site 


<li>Lalbhai Dalpatbhai Museum, Calico Museum of Textiles, Sabarmati Ashram, Akshardham Temple are all accessible within ~30–40 min drive 

</ul>
<h3> 6. Recent Local Governance Updates 🛡️</h3>
<ul>
<li>AMC recently resolved waterlogging in Gopal Chowk (Nikol) by installing a new stormwater line 


<li>However, mosquito-breeding concerns led to sealing a construction project in Nikol area 

</ul>
<h3> 7.  Summary ✅</h3>
<ul>
<li>Feature	Overview
<li>Location	Eastern Ahmedabad; excellent connectivity
<li>Affordability	₹3 000–₹5 000 / sq ft purchase; ₹3 000–₹20 000 rent
<li>Amenities	Schools, hospitals, malls, parks within reach
<li>Growth	High appreciation; real estate boom
<li>Challenges	Traffic, parking, seasonal infrastructure strains
<li>Community	Family-friendly, safe, well-lit, green
</ul>
<ul>
<h3>In short:</h3> 
<li>Nikol is a modern, well-connected, and family-oriented neighborhood in eastern Ahmedabad—ideal for both residents and investors. It offers abundant amenities, strong growth potential, and a pleasant living environment, though price points and infrastructural updates are still catching up with the rapid pace of development.
</ul>
</p>
